snippet: Human error and a malfunctioning control system are to blame for a November drone accident off the coast of Southern California that injured two sailors and caused $30 million in damage to a warship, the Navy said in a newly unclassified report....

headline.print_headline: Navy: Human Error Partly to Blame for Drone Crash
headline.main: Navy: Human Error Partly to Blame for Drone Crash

lead_paragraph: Human error and a malfunctioning control system are to blame for a November drone accident off the coast of Southern California that injured two sailors and caused $30 million in damage to a warship, the Navy said in a newly unclassified report.
